The lattice shown is continued for $9$ rows. What will be the third number in the $9$th row? \begin{tabular}{rccccc}
Row 1: & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5 \\
Row 2: & 6 & 7 & 8 & 9 & 10 \\
Row 3: & 11 & 12 & 13 & 14 & 15 \\
Row 4: & 16 & 17 & 18 & 19 & 20
\end{tabular}

Fourteen white cubes are put together to form the figure on the right.  The complete surface of the figure, including the bottom, is painted red.  The figure is then separated into individual cubes.  How many of the individual cubes have exactly four red faces?

[asy]
size(150);
pair a=(1,0),b=(0,1),c=(0.45,0.4);

void drawcube(pair loc){
     filldraw(loc+b--loc--loc+a--loc+a+c--loc+a+b+c--loc+b+c--cycle,white);
     draw(loc+b--loc+a+b--loc+a+b+c^^loc+a+b--loc+a);
}

pair location[]={origin,b,a,2a,3a,3a+b,-c,3a-c,-2c,-2c+b,-2c+a,-2c+2a,-2c+3a,-2c+3a+b};

for(int i; i<14;++i){
   drawcube(location[i]);
}


[/asy]

What is the shortest distance that can be travelled if you start at any point, $A$, $B$, $C$, or $D$, and visit the other three points once?

[asy]
pair A,B,C, D;
A = (-3,3); B = (3,0); C = (0, -4); D = (0,0);
draw(D--B--C--cycle); draw(D--A--B--cycle);draw(D--A--C--cycle);
label("$A$", A, NW);label("$B$", B, E); label("$C$", C, S);label("$D$", D, NE);
label("3", D--B, S); label("6", A--B, NE); label("6", A--C, SW); label("4", D--C, NW+N);
label("5", A--D, SE+NE); label("5", C--B, E);
[/asy]

