Three congruent isosceles triangles $DAO$, $AOB$ and $OBC$ have $AD=AO=OB=BC=10$ and $AB=DO=OC=12$.  These triangles are arranged to form trapezoid $ABCD$, as shown.  Point $P$ is on side $AB$ so that $OP$ is perpendicular to $AB$.

[asy]

pair A, B, C, D, O, P;

A= (6, 8);

B=(18, 8);

C=(24, 0);

D=(0,0);

O=(12,0);

P=(12,8);

draw(A--B--C--D--A);

draw(A--O--B);

draw(O--P, dashed);

label("A", A, NW);

label("B", B, NE);

label("C", C, SE);

label("D", D, SW);

label("O", O, S);

label("P", P, N);

label("12", (D+O)/2, S);

label("12", (O+C)/2, S);

label("10", (A+D)/2, NW);

label("10", (B+C)/2, NE);

[/asy]

